<TEXT>
a fort worth bishop has called for 
recognition of a church within a church as a haven for 
conservative episcopalians opposed to such socalled liberal trends 
as the ordination of women 
let us firmly declare and commit ourselves to the episcopal 
church and to the provinces of the anglican communion that it is 
our will to be the church within the church the rt rev 
clarence pope jr said thursday 
pope bishop of the diocese of fort worth and president of the 
evangelical and catholic mission addressed nearly 1200 delegates 
at the opening session of the episcopal synod of america on 
thursday 
pope is president of the evangelical and catholic mission and 
he and other bishops in the mission called the synod last year 
after the rev barbara harris was consecrated as the first female 
bishop in the episcopal church 
the bishops called ms harris election the final crisis 
pope and other speakers contended that segments of the episcopal 
church are abandoning the biblical faith through decisions to 
ordain female priests and bishops and efforts to relax moral 
teachings on sexuality and marriage 
we must do all we can to remain within this church and do all 
we can to transform this church said the rt rev johndavid 
schofield of the diocese of san joachin fresno calif if it 
will not be permitted then we will have to take the next step when 
it comes 
pope said the episcopal churchs laws do not prevent the 
traditionalists from forming a voluntary association and he called 
for the acceptance of the new organization as a way for 
traditionalists to stay within the church 
we seek nothing more and nothing less than to provide a way to 
maintain and propagate the gospel of jesus christ through the 
unchanged tradition of the historic church society we 
believe is hungry for this kind of church and gospel neither of 
which is subject to the shifting sands of this present age pope 
said 
popes proposal would create a voluntary organization that would 
allow traditionalist bishops and priests to visit parishes 
traditionalist bishops a small minority in the 29 millionmember 
episcopal church say the church has lost 1 million members in the 
past two decades because of liberal changes including the 
ordination of women 
</TEXT>
