noted artist erte will collect big 
money in atlantic city but not by gambling 
i am bored by gambling the master of art deco design said 
instead erte will exhibit and sell some of his private 
collection in a casino ballroom tonight 
in his suite at trump castle hotel and casino this week the 
96yearold artist was signing special exhibit books for high 
rollers who are invited to see and bid on ertes special exhibit 
on sunday the exhibit will be open to the public and available 
for purchase 
the collection includes 50 original watercolors some up to 80 
years old it will also feature some of ertes distinctive 
sculptures and jewelry and a costume recently designed by the 
artist for the new broadway musical stardust 
born romain de tirtoff the artist took the name erte from his 
initials today the tiny whitehaired man who designs his own 
suits and chunky jewelry smiled when asked if he has any favorites 
among his pieces 
they are all my children and i am their father he said 
but he admitted to some affection for one abstract sculpture in 
his paris flat titled autumn 
i will never give it away because it is the center of my 
decorations he said 
the artist said he has created almost 20000 designs mostly of 
women bedecked in elaborate outfits and ertes mind and 
paintbrushes keep flowing 
retirement is to die and i dont want to die he said i 
will retire when i die 
erte who is building a new home in majorca spain has spent 
most of his years in a paris apartment said eric estorick 
managing director of the grosvenor gallery in london ertes 
exclusive world agent 
there have been five different owners of his flat who spent 
years waiting for him to die estorick said chuckling 
erte keeps living a full life traveling around the world to 
exhibits and designing costumes and scenery for upcoming theater 
productions 
i always make the complete package for a show he said i 
hate to make costumes for someone elses setting if one painter 
makes the background and one the costumes its not art its an 
accommodation 
the end results are richly colored costumes and headpieces 
melding with spectacular background effects 
erte said he first started drawing at age 3 at 6 he drew an 
evening dress that his mother later had a dressmaker copy for her 
to wear years later from 1915 to 1937 he created covers and 
illustrations for harpers bazaar 
he never married yet he has created thousands of dreamlike 
images of women with inspiration that he said comes from heaven 
estorick said erte is not only a meticulous creator but 
unlike fashion designers he is a basic designer and an artist 
other designers have to bring in artists to flesh out their ideas 
even with the foibles of old age rheumatic problems and old 
teeth the fact is that erte is a discipline machine he always is 
a nononsense hardworking artist estorick said 
