the veterans affairs department is reducing 
its home mortgage interest rates by half a percentage point a move 
that could save purchasers more than 300 a year on a typical va 
loan of 75000 
effective monday the maximum interest rate for the federally 
backed loans will drop to 10 percent it is the first change in the 
va rate since dec 19 when the rate rose from 10 percent to 105 
percent 
va home loans may be used to purchase improve or refinance a 
home or condominium and to purchase or refinance a manufactured 
home 
secretary edward j derwinski said the action reflects 
continued investor confidence in the economy as well as current 
financial market conditions in which investors are willing to 
accept lower yields on longterm investments 
the department said that effective monday a variety of other 
mortgage rates also will fall by a halfpoint the maximum rate for 
graduatedpayment mortgages will fall to 1025 percent home 
improvement loans 115 percent manufactured home loans 125 
percent manufactured home lotonly loans 12 percent and 
manufactured home and lot loans 12 percent 
