senate judiciary committee joseph biden says 
the american bar association may have too much influence in the 
selection of federal judges a position that puts him in partial 
agreement with conservative critics 
in some respects the abas standing committee has become 
larger than life biden said friday at a hearing of his 
committee he was referring to the abas standing committee on 
federal judiciary 
surely the judiciary committee has over the years given the 
aba standing committee an exalted status he said but biden also 
said that the abas opinion on judges was sought in the past 
because cronyism and not competence was all too often the reason 
for choosing a nominee 
biden spoke the same day that attorney general dick thornburgh 
told reporters he considered his dispute with the aba over judicial 
selection to be settled 
thornburgh told reporters he regarded an agreement reached with 
the bar group last month to be dispositive of this issue 
conservative senators have been smoldering ever since four of 
the standing committees 15 members voted to find thenjudge robert 
bork unqualified for a seat on the us supreme court 
joined by a number of other lawmakers conservative senators 
have been calling for an overhaul or even an end to the process 
under which the committee meets behind closed doors and does not 
explain how it arrives at its conclusions or how the individual 
committee members voted 
the system sen gordon humphrey rnh told the judiciary 
committee is a moldering corrupted malodorous old relic which 
should be given a quick burial for the sake of public health 
sen orrin hatch rutah told the judiciary committee it is 
no longer appropriate that this one private organization be granted 
a status not accorded to any other group 
it exercises a virtual veto over judicial nominees hatch 
said 
but sen howard m metzenbaum dohio scoffed at what he called 
conservative concerns over the abas liberal focus he said he had 
been an aba member for decades and theres no question about it 
i would put the aba on the conservative side 
who are you kidding metzenbaum said this is the 
hierarchy of all the big corporate law firms in the country 
under the new agreement with the aba the group promised to drop 
a disputed paragraph from a brochure outlining its methods of 
reviewing potential nominees for the federal bench 
the paragraph to be erased says political or ideological 
philosophy are not considered except to the extent that they may 
bear upon other factors 
far from barring consideration of politics critics say the 
paragraph specifically opens the door to such inquiries 
aba officials also promised to refrain from weighing the 
ideology and political philosophy of potential candidates for judge 
whose names are sent to it for review by the department of justice 
the officials however made a point of adding they had never 
considered those factors in their evaluations 
names of potential federal judges are sent to the president by 
senators and other influential officials before they are nominated 
by the president they are evaluated by the administration and 
investigated by the fbi 
since 1953 the government also has maintained an arrangement 
under which potential candidates are screened by the aba the major 
professional association of the nations lawyers before the 
president sends their names to capitol hill for confirmation by the 
senate 
