<TEXT>
with much fanfare authorities sunday are opening 
a sevenmile stretch of interstate 90 that has the dubious 
distinction of being the most expensive segment of freeway ever 
built 
it is part of a 146 billion highway project for the 
mushrooming seattle metropolis to build roads that probably will be 
badly congested by the time they are completed in 1994 
for the time being the new link between seattle and bellevue 
across lake washington brings welcome relief from the twicedaily 
creep across the lakes two existing fourlane spans that become 
jammed by fenderbenders 
commuters also say goodbye to an infamous i90 lane that 
switched direction depending on the commute with no barrier to 
separate traffic motorists tagged it the death lane 
the completed segment includes a floating bridge a 
tripledecker tunnel with one level for bicycles and pedestrians 
and a concreteslab roof over sections of the highway that will be 
landscaped as parks 
the freeway proposed in 1957 drew the wrath of residents who 
wanted to protect neighborhoods and of environmentalists 
in 1971 planners agreed to scale back the project and build 
tunnels on the seattle side of the lake but an environmental 
impact statement wasnt approved until 1979 
by then federal money had dried up and it wasnt until 
congress raised the gas tax in 1982 that funds became available 
construction began in earnest the next year 
so far 860 million has been spent the balance of the money 
will go to reopening and linking up one of the old bridges located 
to the south of the new structure as well as other additions 
at about 200 million a mile the freeway has set a record for 
costliness but one that will soon fall to a project at i90s 
other terminus boston according to seattle project manager brian 
henkel 
that 44 billion project will rebuild interstate 93 through 
downtown boston and construct a third harbor tunnel to link i90 
with logan international airport 
despite a major crisis every second day henkel said he is 
on time and 16 million under budget the project includes the 
worlds largest softground tunnel 1500 feet long and 63 feet in 
diameter henkel said 
henkel said he still sees vestiges of the rancor that surrounded 
the project 
but now its almost opposite to the earlier emotion of make 
the freeway as difficult as possible to get on and maybe they wont 
build it he said now they say i live in seattle and work 
on the eastside and theres no way i can get on i90 conveniently 
