<TEXT>
eighteen years after authorities say john 
e list methodically shot his family to death people here see an 
end to the tale that has haunted this quiet wealthy suburb 
the former sunday school teacher was arrested in richmond va 
last thursday where he had been living with a second wife of four 
years and working as an accountant 
nearly two decades of leadchasing in every state europe and 
south america were terminated by a simple anonymous tip following a 
broadcast of the case on the television show americas most 
wanted 
police chief anthony scutti said the murders left a black mark 
on the town of 32000 25 miles from new york city the arrest 
helped fade that mark 
if they had a giant microphone in town you would have heard a 
giant sigh of relief scutti said when the chief went to an 
awards dinner the night of the arrest he was greeted with a 
spontaneous standing ovation 
i think that reflected the feeling of all of us he said 
on dec 7 1971 police who had been alerted by worried 
neighbors found the bodies of lists wife and three children lying 
on sleeping bags on the ballroom floor of the familys 18room 
mansion cloths covered the faces of helen 45 patricia 16 john 
jr 15 and frederick 13 the body of lists 85yearold mother 
alma was found in an upstairs closet 
all five had been shot in the head they apparently had been 
dead nearly a month list who had held jobs as an accountant and 
insurance salesman and was apparently beset by financial and family 
problems had vanished 
in many ways the list case worked its way into the towns 
consciousness teenagers seeking excitement would cruise by the 
house until it mysteriously burned down a year after the deaths 
almost every year newspapers would run articles on the crimes 
anniversary 
and people remembered 
scutti then a sergeant recalled bringing patricia list to the 
stationhouse late one night several months before her death she 
had slipped out the window and was going to meet a friend 
lo and behold he comes in at 230 in the morning dressed in a 
business suit to pick up his daughter scutti said list scutti 
said sometimes dressed the same way to mow his lawn 
claudia haller remembered being interviewed by list for a 
teaching job at the primary school connected with the redeemer 
lutheran church 
the redbrick slateroofed church where list taught sunday 
school was just about the only community tie he had church was a 
constant he used pastors as references for jobs and a gun permit 
three weeks before the crime list met his second wife at a denver 
church function in 1977 authorities said i felt that he was a 
very intellectual man he was just very calm and collected you 
could see he was a very religious man too mrs haller said he 
was also a private man given to eating lunch alone at work said 
westfield detective lt bernard tracy 
now that one mystery lists whereabouts has been solved 
another remains why 
list left letters as yet undisclosed to his pastor and others 
explaining his actions list reportedly believed his family was 
falling away from their religion and had to be killed for their own 
good 
a newspaper at the time included quotations from brenda taylor 
helen lists daughter by a previous husband who had died in the 
korean war miss taylor said the marriage with list was filled with 
tension because her mother was psychologically unstable and had a 
drinking problem 
lists lutheran pastor in rochester ny during the early 
1960s said more tension was created by mrs lists comparison of 
the meek list with her first husband a strong military man 
toward the end mrs list was bedridden for months and lists 
financial problems were mounting he was upset with his daughters 
desire to become an actress and attachment to a young man 
considered in the wrong crowd said james moran police chief 
at the time 
the young man for several years left flowers at the familys 
grave in fairview cemetery where a single headstone records lists 
wife and children 
i hope it ends for him more than it does for us said mark 
pletscher of fanwood who was two years behind john jr in school 
i hope he comes to grips with this whole thing 
</TEXT>
