a sailor who went absent without leave 
during the vietnam war 20 years ago is a dinosaur from a 
different era and should not be courtmartialed his attorney 
argued 
charles smith who walked away from the treasure island base and 
his wife and child in 1969 was tracked down by the navy last month 
smith 40 is charged with desertion and using marijuana the 
drug charge was added because smith tested positive for marijuana 
when he surrendered may 4 navy officials said 
if courtmartialed and convicted smith faces up to seven years 
in prison 
at a friday hearing to determine whether smith should be 
courtmartialed or simply discharged his attorney howard de nike 
said the man you see before you is sort of a dinosaur 
someone from a different era 
when smith went awol from the base near here he was 19 naive 
and angry that his wife had been unfaithful de nike said 
smith remarried fathered five children and became a respected 
foreman at a paint company 
basically we dont have the same person today that we had 
then de nike said arguing that smith should be granted the same 
discharge awol servicemen received under amnesty programs during 
the 1970s 
