the prosecutors also cited a lack of physical evidence or 
corroborating testimony for her account 
in response to a freedom of information act request by the 
associated press the us attorneys office released a copy a 
sept 1 1987 letter explaining the outcome to lawrence baskir 
attorney for kari tupper 
the letter was signed by charles h roistacher executive 
assistant to thenus attorney joseph digenova 
a former legislative aide and the daughter of longtime adams 
family friends ms tupper now 27 said in september of last year 
