<TEXT>
smoke from burning vehicles cast a pall over 
tiananmen square sunday morning after violence that will leave a 
permanent scar on china 
the numbers of dead and wounded from military attacks on 
demonstrators were estimated in the hundreds massive arrests are 
inevitable along with purges in the communist party leadership 
the military action made it clear the government was willing to 
use brutal force against mainly unarmed and peaceful demonstrators 
to ensure the privileges and power of an aging leadership and to 
perpetuate the political system 
deng xiaoping chinas 84yearold senior leader may have 
forfeited his place as one of the 20th centurys great statesmen 
